article.description: Sam Houston State dominates Jarvis Christian 98-48
article.headline: Sam Houston State dominates Jarvis Christian 98-48
article.linkText: Sam Houston State dominates Jarvis Christian 98-48
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas -- Kaheem Ransom led four teammates with double-digit scoring Wednesday night and Sam Houston State cruised to a 98-48 win over NAIA Jarvis Christian to remain unbeaten. Ransom scored 16 points for the Bearkats (4-0), Dakarai Henderson had 15, Michael Holyfield and Aurimas Majauskas each scored 12 and Paul Baxter added 11. The Bearkats bench outscored Jarvis Christian's starters 55-48. Leading Bearkats scorer Jabari Peters, averaging 22.5 points per game, didn't score in 20 minutes of play but had six assists. Baxter opened the game with a 3-pointer and the Bearkats never trailed. Holyfield grabbed a game-high 12 rebounds and blocked three shots. The Bearkats outrebounded the Bulldogs 51-25 and outshot them 60 percent to 29.8 percent from the field on 33-of-55 shooting. Dewayne Wade led Jarvis Christian with eight points. Sam Houston State's 4-0 start is their best since beginning the 2008 season with a 10-0 run.
